blog.name: sorrybabypodcast
blog.title: Sorry, Baby: A Killing Eve Podcast
blog.description:
Welcome to the Tumblr home of Sorry, Baby: A Killing Eve Podcast. 
"Do you like listening or being listened to?" Both.

summary:
Hello KE Fandom!
We are well into hiatus (not you, UK bunnies) - and what better way to count-down to April, 2020 than by...
body:
Hello KE Fandom!

We are well into hiatus (not you, UK bunnies) - and what better way to count-down to April, 2020 than by reliving the journey of the show we all obsess over!

We are Sorry Baby - a fan-made Killing Eve podcast that is dedicated to peeling back the layers of this totally focussed, and yet, sometimes inaccessible show. Join us, as we deep dive into every episode and find parallels in Eve and Villanelle’s intersections and contradictions.

We are now live on ALL platforms: Apple Podcast, Google Podcasts, Stitcher, Amazon - and any other podcast streaming app that you use. To start you off, here is the Spotify link: https://open.spotify.com/show/316bpHGUHqPcNSiBzKCW7D

We have just uploaded our detailed review of S1XE1 - Nice Face! We intend to be spoiler free, so all of you new listeners can join in on the ride - but there will be more than enough for the binge watchers to chew on, so watch out for the veiled references and things we sneak into the analysis.

Here is everything you need to know:

When will you upload it? Every Tuesday!

Where can we find you? Every Podcast platform!

But, 2 hours - why? Because Eve should have heated that Shepherd’s Pie in the oven! We take our time digging in, and we hope it’s worth yours!

I have so many thoughts, can I share them? Of course! We started this so we could engage with all the brilliant fans out there. Reach us at: [killingeveflyonthewall@gmail.com](mailto:killingeveflyonthewall@gmail.com), DM us here on reddit, Twitter: @sorrybabypod, Tumblr: https://sorrybabypodcast.tumblr.com/

We want all your feedback, all your enthusiasm, and all your questions! Please send them out on any of the platforms mentioned above. We are taking in questions for all of Season 1 - so please help us make the listener section a success! And lastly, Subscribe, share, and post reviews wherever you like your voice being heard!

“Do you like listening, or being listened to?” Both.

xx
